 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhrono85.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khrono85</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/8/01 11:19:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drogan Warlord Skargus. (chardok quests) SPOILER!!</span><hr size=1> Ok here is my Fast run down to help anyone who is ally get chardok rings. I am to busy to copy and paste all the chat lines, etc, etc, so this is the quick pay attention version on how to do it.<br>
<br>
<br>
1.) Be, or Get ally To chardok. kill millions upon millions of goblins in droga, nurga, etc. And you can hand in death mt salts, Goblin skins to quest guy after you become dubious.<br>
<br>
2. After Becoming Ally to chardok, talk to quest guy  in front of the zone. Hail him. Follow the text story Script. Then Say I Serve The Sarnak. And get ring 1.<br>
<br>
Ring 1 completed.  AC+2 Charisma+1 Wis+1 int+1 hp+65 Mana+45. Pretty awesome ring IMO.<br>
<br>
Ok, off for ring 2. I Completed this as soon as the servers came up yesterday. Taking Claim as the 1st one :-P unless anyone can prove otherwise. Ok, Goto Droga, There is a new goblin which was implemented down near the Warder area, where shrouds drop. Name is a Goblin Traitor. If you are ally to chardok, you will be ally to this Goblin. Hail him. Follow the story Text, etc, etc, etc. Get the note he give you, Take it outside to the  Sarnak Spy. He is just left and a long the mt to the left out from Droga. Give him the note you got from the Goblin traitor. Follow the story line, etc, etc, etc. At the end tell  him you will get the report, etc, etc. He gives you another note. Now you have to go back down in Droga, and just kill random goblins to get the Warlords insignia shield. It was stupid common yesterday after the patch, dropped like every 3-4 goblins. It is a no drop shield, no stats, etc. Take this shield, and the forged note you got from the sarnak spy, and head to Warsliks woods, just outside near Cablis. There is another new Goblin there called a Shady goblin. He is up the ramp a bit near outskirts of Cablis/warsliks. Hail him, follow the story, hand him the shield, and forged sarnak spy report. He give you Skargus report. Take that, and head back to droga again. Now, this is where you will need help. I completed this with 1 cleric.   So me,  (60 druid) and (58 cleric) did this, but was very hard, and almost died. We didn't know how tuff the mob was, but he was! Was a Sk, blue to me at 60,  Hts, and hits for 170's.  Ok, So, go back down to droga, and head near chief Rukgus area. up the ramp a few rooms away from chief, somewhere between soothsayer camp, and rukgus, is another goblin named, The Angry Goblin. This is the old Warlord Gar-something or other, who got banished, etc.  When you are ready to do battle, med up have all members in the party ready to help you, and hand in the skargus report to him. I would invis up, so you do not get adds like I did, and follow the angry Goblin as he spawns Drogan Warlod Skargus. There are quite a bit of number of goblins to the walk thru to get to him, so either invis, or plan before, and clear the whole way throug, so you can have an easier fight then I did. Ok, now. Kill Drogan warlord skargus, loot his head, go back to chardok. Hail the quest guy again. Follow the script again just in case. And then Hand in Ring 1, and Skargus head. You get ring 2. Forgot name of it at the moment :-P.<br>
<br>
Stats are for Ring 2.  AC+5 Stam+5 Hp+85! Mana+50! <br>
                             Charis+2 Wis+2 Int+2.  5 charges of DS<br>
<br>
That is one nice ring if you ask me. 100 hp ring 50 mana, and very good stats and AC<br>
<br>
You can also follow the story script again, and get Ring 1 again. AC+2 charis+1 wis+1 int+1 hp+65 mana+45., and wear both Like I am doing. Switching out tons of items, etc, , and wearing both rings. I have increased my hp OVER 200+hp.<br>
<br>
Unfortunetly at this time there seems to be only 2 rings implemented. Ring is amazing stats IMO. Maybe they will put more in in the future who knows. Final notes: Like I said, I did this 60 druid, with a friend 58 cleric, and also a nearby friendly enchanter gave us C2 at the Very end of the battle, which helped a little. If you plan to do this, take a druid so he can root him, which he resisted 50% of the time or more, cleric, tank, etc. If you are very high level, I would go down with 3 the least. If you are low level get a whole group at least.  Hope this helps everyone who is ally get their rings.<br>
<br>
Good Luck.<br>
<br>
Khrono Level 60 Hierophant.<br>
Guardians Of Light. Saryrn Server.<br>
